OL,4,Csurgery and enduring a decade of pain
OL,6,FDuring that time his position on the
OL,7,Fwaiting list was reset in error and he
OL,8,Fwas also removed from the list
OL,9,Fentirely by
OL,11,FFor "Mr D", he was removed from the
OL,12,Fwaiting list when he missed surgical
OL,13,Fappointments because he was in
OL,14,Fhospital undergoing treatment for
OL,15,Fanother illness.
OL,17,FDespite provision in the guidance for
OL,18,Fthis type of situation, Mr D was
OL,19,Fremoved from the list and was waiting
OL,20,Fto be "treated in turn" which appears
OL,21,Fto be outside of the process.
