OL,6,FMr D received treatment in January
OL,7,F2024, more than five years after being
OL,8,Fadded to the list for surgery. Mr D is
OL,9,Fsaid to have experienced a lot of
OL,10,Fpain, which affected his wellbeing
OL,11,Fsignificantly.
OL,13,F'Patients had their hopes falsely
OL,14,Fraised that surgery would happen soon'
OL,16,FIn its findings, the ombudsman
OL,17,Fdiscovered that the current waiting
OL,18,Ftime for orthopaedic surgery at the
OL,19,FHealth Board is more than four years.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G11/20
