OL,3,CWoman shares woes of cancelled hip
OL,4,Csurgery and enduring a decade of pain
OL,6,FIt also found that the Health Board
OL,7,Fhas had issues including not enough
OL,8,Fstaff, not enough suitable places to
OL,9,Foperate, unclear management
OL,10,Farrangements, and unclear processes
OL,11,Ffor these operations.
OL,13,FIt says the complainants were also put
OL,14,Fthrough the stress and pain of pre-
OL,15,Foperative assessments. These had
OL,16,Ffalsely raised their hopes that
OL,17,Fsurgery would happen soon.
OL,19,FCommenting on the report, the Public
OL,20,FServices Ombudsman for Wales, Michelle
OL,21,FMorris, has said:
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G12/20
