OL,4,Csurgery and enduring a decade of pain
OL,6,F"While patients are waiting for
OL,7,Fsurgery on the list, they should be
OL,8,Ftreated fairly in relation to the
OL,9,Fmanagement of their place on that
OL,10,Flist, how they are communicated with
OL,11,Fabout the time it is likely to take to
OL,12,Freceive treatment and to have their
OL,13,Fexpectations fairly managed.
OL,15,F"Patients who are already facing
OL,16,Flengthy waiting times should feel able
OL,17,Fto rely on the Health Board to manage
OL,18,Fthe waiting list well and in
OL,19,Faccordance with the waiting list
OL,20,Fguidelines.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G13/20
